   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <note>
               <table>
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Electric Shock Hazard</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Hot Surfaces </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Battery and Materials Inside Fence Can Be Toxic </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Avoid injury during startup. </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p/>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Only authorized and trained personnel can enter the fenced area and work on the AGV.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Personnel must wear the appropriate PPE around the AGV.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>The AGV must be stopped before personnel can enter the fenced area where the AGV operates.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Observe all plant and equipment safety requirements.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Turn the AGV off if a safety or operational issue occurs.  Open the door to the fenced area to break the circuit.</p>
            <p>
               <note type="note">
                  <p>The AGV has an E-Stop button on the left side, with an indicator light.</p>
               </note>
               <p>
                  <fig>
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Turn off power to the AGV before working on it.  Then lockout-tagout-verify the power.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>When working on high-voltage assemblies:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Ground the supply cable after disconnecting the voltage.</li>
                  <li>Short-circuit the components, e.g., capacitors by means of a ground rod.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Only install original or Hegla-approved spare parts.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
